<body>
    <%- include('navbar') %>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Suppression Application Documentation</h1>

        <h2>1. Login Using Credentials</h2>
        <p>Use your credentials to log in to the application.</p>

        <h2>2. Master Suppression</h2>
        <p>Upload an Excel file with the required column header names (Company Name, First Name, Last Name, Email ID, Phone Number, linkedinLink).</p>
        <p>Ensure the file format is Excel (.xlsx), and fields should have the above mentioned column headers else the platform will throw an error.</p>
        <p>Select the required client code filter (options include ALL, TE16, D131, HN36, AD62, AN12, DY78, MA99, NT26, UE88).</p>
        <p>Choose the date filter (6 months / 1 year) for the suppression date check.</p>
        <p>Upload the Excel file, and the application will generate an updated Excel file with three additional columns:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Match Status: Indicates whether the entry was found in the database or not.</li>
            <li>Client Code Status: Indicates if the entry was found in the database using the client code.</li>
            <li>Date Status: Provides three status options:
                <ul class="status-options">
                    <li>Fresh Lead GTG: Indicates that the leads are good to go.</li>
                    <li>Still Suppressed: Indicates that the leads are still in suppression.</li>
                    <li>Suppression Cleared: Indicates that the suppression for the leads has been cleared.</li>
                </ul>
                <li>Email Status: Indicates whether the email id was match or unmatch.</li>
                <li>Linkedin Link Status: Indicates whether the linkedin link was match or unmatch.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Check Email</h2>
        <p>Check a single email using the client code. The application will provide two outputs: whether the email is present in the suppression or not.</p>
        <p>The database check uses six fields: First Name, Last Name, Company Name, Email, Client Code, and LinkedIn Link. It returns the following statuses:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Match Status: Indicates whether the entry was found in the database or not.</li>
            <li>Client Code Status: Indicates if the entry was found in the database using the client code.</li>
            <li>Date Status: Provides three status options:
                <ul class="status-options">
                    <li>Fresh Lead GTG: Indicates that the leads are good to go.</li>
                    <li>Still Suppressed: Indicates that the leads are still in suppression.</li>
                    <li>Suppression Cleared: Indicates that the suppression for the leads has been cleared.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Email Status: Indicates whether the email ID was matched or unmatched.</li>
            <li>LinkedIn Link Status: Indicates whether the LinkedIn link was matched or unmatched.</li>
            <li>Data found status: Indicates whether the Data was Data found in suppression or Data not found in suppression.</li>
        </ul>


        <h2>4. Insert Data (Only for Delivery)</h2>
        <p>Upload an Excel file with the required column header names (date_	month_	campaign_id	client	end_client_name	campaign_name	first_name	last_name	company_name	country	phone	email	linkedin_link	job_title	employee_size	asset	delivery_spoc	left_3	left_4	call_disposition	bcl_ops_tl_name	response_date).</p>
        <p>Ensure the file format is Excel to avoid any errors.</p>
        
